Verification
pgTAP, style/rigor of 076_stock_adjustment_test.sql/077_opening_stock_test.sql (hardcoded UUIDs, BEGIN;/ROLLBACK;, test_results temp table). One SIMPLE company, one location, products covering NONE/BATCH/SERIAL tracking.

078_stock_count_test.sql: fn_stock_count_eligible_products correctly expands a category subtree via fn_category_subtree and applies the nature filter; fn_save_stock_count persists a full worksheet with untouched rows staying is_counted=false; resuming (second save) correctly reflects newly-typed rows while leaving untouched ones alone; BATCH_QTY_MISMATCH fires on a sum mismatch; fn_submit_stock_count blocks with NO_COUNTED_LINES on an all-untouched worksheet, succeeds and locks otherwise; editing a SUBMITTED count is blocked.

079_stock_count_review_test.sql: (1) an untouched product never appears in fn_compute_stock_count_variance's output even though the ledger has a non-zero balance for it — proves missed ≠ phantom - line; (2) a ledger entry dated AFTER as_of_date does NOT affect computed system_qty, one dated ON/BEFORE it DOES — proves the as-of-date correctness that's the whole point of decision #2; (3) the same batch counted across two different submitted counts sums correctly; (4) the same serial entered in two overlapping counts is counted ONCE, not summed; (5) an unrecognized serial produces is_unknown_serial=true/adjust_flag=NULL and is skipped by Approve (review still posts successfully off remaining lines); (6) exact counted=system produces no line; (7) reservation: Review A picking Count X blocks Review B from picking the same Count X, and un-picking from A's draft correctly frees it for B; (8) a SUBMITTED count at a different location can't be added to a review for another location; (9) end-to-end Approve: rih_stock_adjustment_headers gets the right source_doc_type/no/date, ledger rows post with correct trans_type, the ADJV voucher balances DR=CR, review's posted_adjustment_no/status='APPROVED' set; (10) a - line exceeding a batch/serial's actual system balance still fails with BATCH_INSUFFICIENT_STOCK/SERIAL_NOT_IN_STOCK — proves Approve genuinely routes through fn_post_stock_movement's existing strict check, not a bypass; (11) COST_NOT_ESTABLISHED still blocks an uncosted + line, unchanged; (12) period-lock and future-date guards on as_of_date.

Manual smoke test in the Codespace: two counters do overlapping-product, non-overlapping-zone counts of the same location (one filtered by Category A, one unfiltered) including a batch-tracked product split across both and a serial-tracked product found by only one; submit both; as manager, club them, confirm the variance grid's clubbed totals and per-source drill-down look right, confirm an intentionally-wrong scanned serial shows as an exception and not a phantom line, approve, and confirm the resulting Stock Adjustment (and its GL voucher) is correct end to end.

